('cmcem09ek002110tgd1p6sb3y', 'cmc0apnf90038qoublubz4128', 'James Webb Telescope Discovers and Photographs Its First Exoplanet', 'The James Webb Space Telescope has made its first independent discovery of an exoplanet — TWA 7 b — and captured a direct image of it. This gas giant, with a mass similar to Saturn, is now the lightest exoplanet ever imaged directly. It''s located about 111 light-years away from Earth, orbiting a young star known as TWA 7.\\n\\nThe planet orbits far from its star — roughly 52 times the Earth–Sun distance — and sits within one of three dusty rings surrounding the star. Using the MIRI instrument with a coronagraph, Webb was able to block out the star''s bright light and isolate the faint glow of the planet.\\n\\nThis marks the first time Webb has discovered a new exoplanet through direct imaging. The achievement demonstrates the telescope''s sensitivity and sets the stage for detecting even smaller, potentially Earth-like worlds in the future.', 'image', 'Tech', 'https://iwzfrnfemdeomowothhn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/posts/images/thumb_5cad1943952e8cdc2c4bed0652818475.webp', 'https://iwzfrnfemdeomowothhn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/posts/5cad1943952e8cdc2c4bed0652818475.webp', false, false, NULL, 'SOL', 1, 0, 0, '2025-06-27 09:28:08.348', '2025-06-28 07:29:39.712'),

('cmcelqt1s001x10tghokwnkqp', 'cmc0apnf90038qoublubz4128', 'Windows Says Goodbye to the Blue Screen of Death.', 'Windows is saying goodbye to one of its most iconic symbols — the Blue Screen of Death (BSOD). In the upcoming Windows 11 update version 24H2, scheduled for summer 2025, Microsoft will replace the blue background with black. This change is part of a broader initiative to improve system reliability after a massive global outage caused by a faulty CrowdStrike update that affected millions of computers.\\n\\nThe new screen will appear cleaner and more modern. The sad face and QR code are gone, the error text has been simplified, and now includes more precise information pointing to the specific driver that caused the crash. A progress indicator in percentage will also be displayed, giving users a better sense of what''s happening during system recovery.\\n\\nThe update will also introduce Quick Machine Recovery — a feature that allows for automatic recovery from serious crashes without manual intervention. This is especially useful for enterprise environments and system administrators who need to restore workstations quickly.\\n\\nThe switch from blue to black is more than just a cosmetic change. It''s a step toward making critical system errors less intimidating for users and easier to diagnose.', 'image', 'Tech', 'https://iwzfrnfemdeomowothhn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/posts/images/thumb_4e78a82a3916e33ddf8d1518a1cc0833.webp', 'https://iwzfrnfemdeomowothhn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/posts/4e78a82a3916e33ddf8d1518a1cc0833.jpg', false, false, NULL, 'SOL', 1, 0, 0, '2025-06-27 09:20:47.248', '2025-06-28 07:29:44.252'),

('cmcel6d1g001h10tgsc1bvto5', 'cmbvtqy84000gqowpvlo2r5tp', 'From Military Roots to Rally Domination: The Audi Quattro Story', 'In the late 1970s, Audi engineers were searching for a way to distinguish themselves from the competition and create something truly innovative. The breakthrough came during winter testing of the Volkswagen Iltis, a military off-road vehicle that displayed remarkable traction thanks to its four-wheel-drive system. One of Audi''s engineers, Jörg Bensinger, observed how easily the Iltis handled snowy terrain and suggested adapting a similar concept for a passenger car.\\n\\nThe idea caught the attention of Audi''s technical director, Ferdinand Piëch, known for his relentless pursuit of engineering excellence. The challenge was to design a compact, lightweight, and efficient permanent all-wheel-drive system suitable for mass production. Instead of using a bulky transfer case, the team created a unique layout with a center differential and a hollow driveshaft that transmitted power to the rear axle.\\n\\nIn 1980, Audi unveiled the first production model equipped with this system — the Audi quattro. The car caused an immediate sensation: a turbocharged sports coupe with aggressive styling and a revolutionary drivetrain. But the true test came on the world rally stage. Despite initial skepticism from competitors, the quattro delivered extraordinary results, providing unmatched grip on gravel, snow, and ice.\\n\\nIn 1982, Audi secured its first WRC victory, and by 1983 and 1984, it had claimed the world championship. The quattro system fundamentally changed rally racing, ended rear-wheel-drive dominance, and set a new performance benchmark. Audi''s innovation quickly became a symbol of technical excellence.\\n\\nOver time, the technology evolved — from mechanical to electronic systems — but the core principle of optimal traction remained. The name "quattro" became synonymous with control, stability, and engineering superiority, shaping Audi''s identity around progress and precision.', 'image', 'Tech', 'https://iwzfrnfemdeomowothhn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/posts/images/thumb_2cd1b03564a5012bedf1c86b008db2cb.webp', 'https://iwzfrnfemdeomowothhn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/posts/2cd1b03564a5012bedf1c86b008db2cb.jpg', false, false, NULL, 'SOL', 1, 0, 0, '2025-06-27 09:04:53.38', '2025-06-28 08:15:29.436'),

