('cmcbuya0w007evwbr44ouavgm', 'cmc0apnf90038qoublubz4128', 'Flynn: The First Artificial Intelligence Enrolled in University', 'In 2025, the University of Applied Arts in Vienna became the first educational institution in the world to officially enroll an artificial intelligence in a full academic program. This AI, named Flynn, was accepted into the Digital Arts department and has set a historic precedent in the world of education and technology.\\n\\nFlynn is not just a chatbot, but a complex system that combines a language model, a visual generator, and speech synthesis modules. It applied like any regular student—submitting a portfolio, passing an interview, and completing an entrance exam. Its work—digital collages and visual narratives created using AI tools—impressed the admissions committee with their originality and artistic vision.\\n\\nThe goal of the project is to explore how AI can participate in education on equal footing with human students: completing assignments, engaging in critiques, and learning theoretical concepts. Flynn is already attending classes, receiving grades, and even joining discussions with students and professors through speech synthesis and chat interface. Although overseen by academic mentors, Flynn is granted a degree of autonomy as part of the experiment.\\n\\nCampus reactions are mixed. Some view it as a bold leap into the future; others express concern over creativity, authorship, and fairness. Key questions arise: Who owns Flynn''s artworks? Can it earn a diploma? What are the ethical boundaries of AI in education?\\n\\nNonetheless, Flynn''s case is already a milestone—a turning point in the relationship between humans and artificial intelligence. Flynn is not just a "student," but a mirror reflecting a future where the lines between technology and human culture grow increasingly blurred.', 'image', 'Tech', 'https://iwzfrnfemdeomowothhn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/posts/images/thumb_37671f1264509d870dff276a8b606a05.webp', 'https://iwzfrnfemdeomowothhn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/posts/37671f1264509d870dff276a8b606a05.webp', false, false, NULL, 'SOL', 6, 0, 0, '2025-06-25 11:15:13.856', '2025-06-26 01:14:40.239'),

('cmcbuoj3f007avwbrlbith3p8', 'cmc0apnf90038qoublubz4128', 'The Origin of the Word "Hacker"', 'The term "hacker" originated in the 1960s at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT). It came from the word "hack," meaning to cut roughly, and evolved into student slang for clever technical work or creative engineering solutions. At MIT, a hacker was someone who found imaginative ways to solve problems in programming and electronics. This culture of inventive thinking was later reflected in The Jargon File and in Steven Levy''s book Hackers: Heroes of the Computer Revolution.\\n\\nEven earlier, in the 1920s, "hack" was used to describe amateur or rough work. By the 1960s, the term had become a compliment for skilled programmers who could "hack" a system not to damage it, but to explore and improve it.\\n\\nIn the 1970s and 1980s, the meaning of the word began to shift. Some individuals, known as "phreakers," started using technical knowledge to manipulate telephone systems. As media attention grew, "hacker" started to be associated with computer crime. By the early 1980s, the word was widely viewed in a negative light.\\n\\nThe tech community responded by proposing distinctions based on intent: white hat hackers for ethical professionals, black hats for malicious attackers, and grey hats for those operating in between. Still, the broader public often continued to link the word "hacker" with illegal activity.\\n\\nToday, the word carries both meanings. In the tech world, it still refers to a curious, creative expert. In popular usage, it often implies a criminal. Despite the shift in perception, the original idea behind hacking remains—an expression of curiosity, ingenuity, and the drive to understand how things work.', 'image', 'Tech', 'https://iwzfrnfemdeomowothhn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/posts/images/thumb_db1766d01290fc85d666b6b70ae01417.webp', 'https://iwzfrnfemdeomowothhn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/posts/db1766d01290fc85d666b6b70ae01417.webp', false, false, NULL, 'SOL', 5, 0, 0, '2025-06-25 11:07:39.051', '2025-06-25 15:11:39.448'),

